# Create a new file in this fashion

* Go to your user account in GitHub, https://github.com/"Your user Name"
* Click on an existing repository that you have such as datasciencecoursera or whatever
* The window refreshes showing files in the repo etc.
* Click on the + sign next to the repo name
* This opens a dialog where the new file can be named and edited
* Text can be entered into this file too
* This file is saved as a .md file
